+Summary (final):
+Taiwan constraint enforcement + liquidity/slippage reason code rework completed.
+All 11 Taiwan constraint types enforced in TaiwanMarketConstraints.check().
+Liquidity insufficient has explicit reason code (liquidity_insufficient) for
+both reduce-size and no-trade scenarios. Slippage excessive has deterministic
+threshold (max_allowed_slippage=0.05) that blocks trade with slippage_excessive
+reason code. Cash_insufficient and risk_budget_exhausted reason codes added
+for sizing limit tracing. 32/32 tests pass (22 Taiwan + 10 liquidity/slippage).
+
+Rework history:
+  stage 1 (commit 01d6f27): Taiwan constraint enforcement gap closed
+  stage 2 (current commit): liquidity/slippage reason codes + evidence fix
+
+Taiwan constraint enforcement (TaiwanMarketConstraints.check()):
+  Each violated Taiwan rule produces no-trade (final_qty=0) with specific
+  reason code in violated_rules:
+  price_step, circuit_breaker, suspended, disposition_stock, collection_auction,
+  t_plus_2, near_limit_up, near_limit_down, odd_lot, position_cap, day_trade_limit
+  Priority: circuit_breaker > suspended > disposition > auction > T+2 >
+            near_limit > odd_lot > price_step > position_cap > day_trade_limit
+
+Liquidity insufficient (ExecutionSizingGuard.calculate()):
+  When max_by_liquidity < quantity, veto_reason includes "liquidity_insufficient"
+  reduce-size (final_qty > 0 but limited) or no-trade (final_qty = 0).
+  Also triggered when avg_daily_volume = 0 or liquidity_score = 0.
+
+Slippage excessive (SlippageEstimator.estimate() + ExecutionSizingGuard.calculate()):
+  estimate() accepts max_allowed_slippage (default 0.05 = 5%).
+  If total_slippage > max_allowed_slippage, veto_reason = "slippage_excessive".
+  ExecutionSizingGuard sets final_qty = 0 when slippage_excessive.
+
+Sizing reason codes (all in veto_reason):
+  liquidity_insufficient - liquidity limit reduced or blocked trade
+  cash_insufficient - cash available insufficient
+  risk_budget_exhausted - risk budget insufficient
+  slippage_excessive - estimated slippage exceeded threshold
+
+Files changed (from previous_rework_commit 01d6f27):
+  modules/decision_prechecklist/execution_sizing_guard.py   (+20)
